{
  "texts": [
    "Another challenge in human-chatbot communication is the human behavior and understanding that needs to be taken into account (Nguyen et al., 2022).",
    "First, compared to human-human interaction, human-chatbot communication was reported to take longer and include shorter messages (Hill et al., 2015).",
    "In addition, there is evidence that human-chatbot messages lack vocabulary richness and can contain profane words (Hill et al., 2015).",
    "However, compared to web surveys with open-ended questions, chatbots were reported to produce longer and richer responses from humans (Xiao et al., 2020b).",
    "Interestingly, some evidence suggests that humans can generate more or better-quality ideas when communicating with a chatbot rather than with a human partner (Hwang and Won, 2021)."
  ]
}